ěó2›››                 ăč14 PYGMIES ăč15›››     Pygmies are small black dudes between 4' and 4'8" tallthat have reddish-brown skin, afros, round heads, flat noses, short legs, long arms, and their guts stick out. That inhabit the jungle areas of Asia and some islands of the Indian and Pacific oceans, but most of them live in Africa.›     African Pygmies were once beleived to live throughout central Africa, but now they live in the tropical rain forests of Burundi, Cameroon, Congo, Gabon, Rwanda, and Zaire. They occupy a much smaller area now than they once did because people invaded their area and cut down the forests to grow crops and stuff. The Pygmies are still losing land today because of the building of roads and towns forces them to. ›     Pygmies live their lives by hunting antelope, birds, buffaloes, elephants, monkeys and other animals. Most hunt by trapping their prey by large nets then wasting them with spears. Others hunt with small bows and poison arrows. The women gather fruits, and veggies like berries, mushrooms, nuts and roots. They also collect honey. ›     Most Pygmies live in small groups less than 100 each that have no form of tribal leadership, they just solve their problems by having a general discussion. They move from area to area when the food supply runs low. ›     Pygmies speak their own language plus the languages of neighboring tribes so they can trade meat and things for knives and other metal tools.›     Pygmies treat the land as the giver of life because it provides clothing, food, protection and shelter, and in return they won't do anything to hurt the land in anyway, shape, or form. 